title: Former Bears cornerback Tim Jennings was a healthy scratch Sunday
text:
Former Chicago cornerback Tim Jennings, who the Bears cut this offseason shortly after signing him to a four-year extension, was a healthy scratch for the Buccaneers on Sunday.
Jennings, a two-time pro bowler, signed a four-year extension with the Bears in 2014.
According to the Tampa Bay Times, Jennings struggled in pass defense in the Buccaneers’ game against Jacksonville last week. He missed a tackle on a 59-yard pass play and also gave up a touchdown.
Jennings had knee surgery in February and was cut from the Bears in August. He signed with former Bears coach Lovie Smith and Tampa Bay shortly after.
From the Tampa Tribune :
Bucs coach Lovie Smith said in the wake of the Bucs victory over Jacksonville that he was “disappointed” in the way Jennings finished the game. A few days later defensive coordinator Leslie Frazier hinted that changes might be coming.
Jennings had a league-leading nine interceptions and 55 tackles for the Bears in 2012 .
